[3
Date: Wed, 16 Aug 2000 18:30:14 -0500
From: H. Larry Penning <bevpenn@fgi.net>
Source: http://www.timesofindia.com/today/17hlth23.htm [edited
The United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) has announced it is to
put on hold all shipments of live pigs and swine products from Britain
following an outbreak of classical swine fever (CSF), the British
Broadcasting Corporation reported on Wednesday.
Canada would follow the U.S. lead in banning both live pigs and pork
imports, the BBC said after interviewing a U.S. Official.
It was not clear what would happen to pork products currently on their way
to North America.
Some 12 000 pigs have been destroyed in England since the outbreak of the
disease was announced last week, and the European Union (EU) has banned all
exports of live English pigs and pig semen.
Pork exports are as yet not affected by this ban.
